flowchart TD
  accTitle: End-to-end IoT pipeline architecture
  accDescr: Data flows from Arduino sensors through a Python bridge to Azure IoT Hub, then splits into direct ADX ingestion for raw telemetry and Stream Analytics for real-time anomaly detection. Anomalies land in ADX while raw data is also archived to blob storage. ADX Dashboards visualize both streams.

  subgraph Device [Device Layer]
    A[Arduino Uno + Sensors]
  end

  subgraph Ingestion [Cloud Ingestion]
    B[Azure IoT Hub]
  end

  subgraph Processing [Stream Processing]
    C[Azure Stream Analytics]
    C2[Anomaly Detection]
  end

  subgraph Storage [Storage]
    direction LR
    D1[ADLS Gen2 — Raw]
    D2[Azure Data Explorer — Curated]
  end

  subgraph Viz [Visualization]
    F[ADX Dashboard]
  end

  subgraph Observability [Observability]
    direction LR
    G1[Azure Monitor]
    G2[Application Insights]
  end

  A -- serial telemetry --> PC[Host PC — Python Bridge]
  PC -- HTTPS --> B
  B -- event stream --> C
  B -- direct ingestion --> D2
  C --> C2
  C -- raw archive --> D1
  C2 -- anomaly results --> D2
  D2 -- KQL queries --> F

  B -. platform metrics .-> G1
  C -. job metrics .-> G1
  PC -. traces and logs .-> G2
